					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">ghostppu:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda $2001<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;and #%11100111<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta $2001 ; turn off ppu<br /><br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda vramlo<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta $2006<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda vramhi<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta $2006<br /><br /><br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda nextletter<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta $2007<br /><br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda #$00<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta $2005<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta $2005<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda $2000<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta $2000&lt;----------------------------------<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda $2001<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;ora #%00011010<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta $2001<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda #$01<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta mode<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;rts<br /></div>
<br />
<br />set a breakpoint at $C170 and you'll see that $00 is the last byte written to $2000, effectively turning NMI generation off.
<br />
<br />i would also store the last values written to $2000/$2001 in variables rather then reading them back.</div>

