						<div class="postbody">Yes, that pushing/popping code is the simplest correct way to save and restore all registers properly. While on the subject, the status flags are automatically pushed on the stack by the processor before entering your interrupt handler, and RTI restores them from the stack, so a php...plp would be redundant and pointless.</div>

